The paper deals with the traveling salesperson problem (TSP) and its linear programming formulations, which are classic topics in computer science. The analysis of the support of the subtour elimination linear programming relaxation is a common technique in TSP research, and it is related to the study of matchings and graph theory. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are likely categories. The paper also presents integrality gap upper bounds, which are related to approximation algorithms and complexity theory, and can be classified under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the hardness of finding improved solutions via local search, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and can be categorized under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
